        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Turning the head to the side with neck flexion compresses the jugular veins, impeding venous return from the brain and increasing ICP. Suctioning itself also transiently increases ICP. The head must remain midline with no neck flexion. All other options are appropriate ICP management strategies."
